A man in his 20s was airlifted to hospital after a serious collision involving a motorbike and a car in Broadstairs, police said.Kent Police is looking for witnesses to the crash between a red, white and black Yamaha Fazer motorbike and a white Ford Fiesta, which happened on Sackett’s Hill, at the junction with St Peter’s Road, at about 15:35 BST on Saturday.The force said the man was in a serious condition and his family have been told.It asked witnesses and anyone with relevant dashcam or CCTV footage to contact police.
